Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.04,0:00:02.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Villar...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.75,0:00:06.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to assist Starck\Nin our battle against Waldlind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.63,0:00:09.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Pavel...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.22,0:00:13.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Union is currently\Nin peace talks with the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.39,0:00:15.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not holding my breath\Nfor the Union to act!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.80,0:00:18.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All we need is for you to make a move!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.31,0:00:22.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once you do, Ozeri and Bultava\Nwill surely secede from the Alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.85,0:00:25.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you do make a move, Lord Villar,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.27,0:00:28.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will convince my father\Nto send troops from Dartania.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.65,0:00:31.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In my opinion, Lord Milza is absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.53,0:00:37.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For Altirk to survive, even if it means\Nbreaking off from the Union,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.08,0:00:38.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we should fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.91,0:00:45.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be a laughingstock for leaving the Union\Nfor not getting my way at the Lords' Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.79,0:00:49.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but I don't wish\Nto break Lord Alexis's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.55,0:00:53.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's Lord Alexis himself\Nwho's trying to destroy us!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:57.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, rather than uphold your honor,\Nchoose the path that allows Altirk to survive!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.14,0:00:59.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Siluca! Refrain yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.52,0:01:04.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot bring myself to betray Lord Alexis.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.06,0:01:08.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It appears I don't need your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.44,0:01:11.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Return to your domain with Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.82,0:01:14.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.58,0:01:19.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.70,0:01:22.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.33,0:01:28.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.71,0:01:35.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What that mage said seemed\Nlike sound advice to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.63,0:01:40.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's my call to make, not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.35,0:01:43.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest you show some restraint, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.77,0:01:47.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should pledge fealty to Lady Marrine\Nimmediately, and agree to be subjugated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.27,0:01:51.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's up to me to decide, not you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.86,0:01:54.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of\Nallying with Marrine Kreische!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.12,0:02:02.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be keeping an eye\Non Lord Pavel's battle till the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.24,0:02:08.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm interested to see how Waldlind will\Nassault the perilous Isthmus of Penelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:46.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't like you to act like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.26,0:03:50.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't see any other way to save Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.44,0:03:56.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's unlikely to avoid a war against the Alliance,\Nso it's a matter of how we prepare, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.44,0:03:59.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It will be hard to change the tides of war,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.36,0:04:02.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so our only hope is to muster\Nas many troops as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.29,0:04:08.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:10.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Starting tomorrow,\NI'll be touring the domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.29,0:04:13.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll be joining me, this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.18,0:04:34.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like they're not ready to accept us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.56,0:04:36.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.52,0:04:41.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, there must be\Na lot of Dimitrie's kin here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.57,0:04:42.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.45,0:04:50.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I plan on heading near the Bultava border.\NLet's move on to the next village.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.25,0:04:52.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.51,0:05:50.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take shelter over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.02,0:06:02.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a sorry sight we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.73,0:06:05.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be good if we're in these wet clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.20,0:06:06.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get changed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.13,0:06:23.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No good. The firewood's damp.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.18,0:06:28.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.68,0:06:30.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. A little.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.18,0:06:32.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.77,0:06:34.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.43,0:06:38.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're not cold now, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.35,0:06:40.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.88,0:07:06.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sitting here like this reminds me of\Nhow I used to camp out in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.67,0:07:11.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, you used to\Nwander all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.51,0:07:12.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.47,0:07:15.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Traveling alone really made me feel lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.81,0:07:20.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to have you by my side, Sir Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.15,0:07:25.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the outcome I had in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:30.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but you've been so swamped lately,\NI wanted to give you a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.16,0:07:34.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After the Lords' Congress and\Nthat thing with Lord Villar,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.37,0:07:36.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it'd be a nice change of scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.41,0:07:38.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that why you brought me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.62,0:07:44.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, since you've been going to Castle Unicorn\Nso much, I guess I was kind of worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.84,0:07:47.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That you'd end up becoming Villar's vassal...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.96,0:07:49.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That'd never happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.34,0:07:52.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You went so far as to give up\Nyour court rank to preserve our contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.22,0:07:57.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you need me,\NI intend to serve you forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.06,0:08:00.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I haven't gotten through to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.94,0:08:03.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.36,0:08:12.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been thoughtful,\Nand risked your life for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.03,0:08:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I've always wanted to live up to that,\Nand tried to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.75,0:08:22.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When Lord Villar tried to\Ntake you away from me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:25.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think twice\Nabout giving up my court rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.25,0:08:29.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You also rescued me\Nfrom the Black Witch's spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.63,0:08:31.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I'd rescue you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.68,0:08:34.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're someone important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.26,0:08:39.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I wanted you to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.02,0:08:42.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.98,0:08:47.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.94,0:08:51.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of my feelings for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.70,0:08:55.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I did have a feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:08:59.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought it might just be\Nme imagining things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.62,0:09:02.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.79,0:09:05.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is an extremely important issue,\Nso I want to make it clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:12.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo, can I take it\Nthat you're in love with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.92,0:09:14.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're really gonna make me go there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.68,0:09:17.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You really are a mage, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.86,0:09:29.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course...\NI'm in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.89,0:10:04.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.15,0:10:17.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.89,0:10:40.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that Shadow-like knight?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.89,0:10:42.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, that's Milza Kuches.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.77,0:10:46.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that's the Black Prince of Dartania.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.91,0:11:01.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we're going to attack the Starck fortress,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:04.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,our only option is to advance along\Na narrow one-way path along the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.83,0:11:07.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, these rocky hills tower over\Nthe path on its eastern side,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.79,0:11:12.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,while there are ten ships with catapults\Nmoored in the sea to the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.88,0:11:18.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,According to my sources, a Dartanian fleet is\Nproviding Lord Pavel with food and supplies,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:20.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and are moored in nearby waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.80,0:11:23.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would be impossible\Nto reach the peninsula by ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.81,0:11:26.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we managed to get there,\Nit won't be easy to defeat Milza.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.68,0:11:31.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What if we climbed the hills,\Nand attacked the fortress from the ridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.65,0:11:33.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if we climb those hills,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.82,0:11:36.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we'll be forced to leave\Nour horses and armor behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.53,0:11:40.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do have one idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.95,0:11:43.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this wetland known as the Rotten Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:46.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,a form of Chaos Hazard\Ncalled miasma appears frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:51.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This miasma can also be\Ngenerated artificially, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.79,0:11:54.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're going to generate\Nmiasma, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.21,0:11:58.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let the wind carry it\Ninto the Isthmus of Penelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.30,0:12:07.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The soldiers will be forced to either\Nforfeit the castle or succumb to the miasma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.89,0:12:11.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then, if we time our attack\Nfor when the miasma clears,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:15.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,even the strongest of fortresses\Nwill be sure to fall in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.19,0:12:19.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using Chaos Hazard is a violation\Nof the Lords' Code!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.07,0:12:22.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't fight fair and square,\Neven if we were to win–
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.11,0:12:23.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.20,0:12:25.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- What?\N- Lady Marrine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.33,0:12:30.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Won't Waldlind come under fire\Nfor using dirty tactics to win?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:33.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of becoming\Na virtuous but inept leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.34,0:12:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I should incur infamy far and wide,\NI intend to hold sway over the continent!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.01,0:12:46.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're prepared, then we will obey\Nyour command and fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.10,0:12:49.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I command you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.60,0:12:52.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Viscount Pavel Murado,\Nand the Lords and soldiers allied to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.85,0:12:55.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,will not be allowed to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.31,0:12:59.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Half-baked benevolence will\Nbe seen as weakness on our part.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.32,0:13:02.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Show the world what becomes\Nof those who defy Waldlind,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.49,0:13:08.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and force the indecisive Lords of Bultava and Ozeri\Nto choose either subjugation or death!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.54,0:13:10.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:18.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have a favor to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.84,0:13:19.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.21,0:13:23.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to contact Milza,\Nthe Prince of Dartania.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.35,0:13:35.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost time for\Nthe wind to change direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.36,0:13:42.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then, let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.78,0:13:45.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A lake bed is a silent thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.53,0:13:48.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, at times, it becomes a vacillating swell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.04,0:13:50.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Swirl!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.42,0:14:02.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Red poison, sweet poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.88,0:14:05.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The poison stagnating in the mud\Nconsume each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.76,0:14:09.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Poison becomes foam, fog, then haze,\Nand is carried by the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.64,0:14:11.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rise up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.28,0:14:26.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.65,0:14:30.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just learned firsthand\Nhow overpowering miasma can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.33,0:14:35.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning there's no question that\Nthe fortress soldiers will be incapacitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.46,0:14:44.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Miasma!\NMiasma's coming this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.80,0:14:54.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cover your mouths with cloths!\NHang in there until the miasma's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.77,0:14:56.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The wind will change direction eventually!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.23,0:14:59.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only we had Lord Milza's help...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.33,0:16:01.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How unfortunate for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.21,0:16:05.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.92,0:16:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...how the continent's\Nmost powerful knights fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.84,0:16:15.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is the Kreische clan's style\Nto fight rationally, that is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.69,0:16:22.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Viscount Pavel Murado.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.27,0:16:25.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I receive thy Crest as my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.13,0:16:47.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not what I was expecting,\Nbut entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.55,0:16:50.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.18,0:16:58.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am Waldlind Margrave Marrine Kreische's\Nlady-in-waiting, Layla.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.06,0:16:59.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The same, Kamhi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:00.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.27,0:17:05.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Milza, our mistress would like\Nto meet with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.40,0:17:08.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Alliance leader, meet with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.67,0:17:28.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what Alexis would think\Nif he hears about this battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.76,0:17:31.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:34.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.05,0:17:38.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what did Crown Prince Milza say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.81,0:17:41.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd like to meet\Ndirectly with you right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.81,0:17:46.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, we were told to bring you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:54.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we bring Dartania into the Alliance fold,\Nwe can never defeat Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.45,0:17:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Villar Constance...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.32,0:18:00.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Turns out he did not have\Nwhat it takes to rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.79,0:18:05.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no use for anyone who\Nlacks the will to unite the continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.18,0:18:23.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Announcing the Margrave of Waldlind,\NFactory Alliance leader, Lady Marrine Kreische.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.35,0:18:27.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am Milza Kuches, Crown Prince of Dartania.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.27,0:18:31.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you seek my aid\Nin uniting the continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.61,0:18:32.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.78,0:18:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My father, Matthias, and I have inherited\Nthe dream envisioned by my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.16,0:18:41.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To unite the continent, and merge all Crests.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.20,0:18:46.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the legend is true, the era of Chaos\Nwill come to an end by doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.33,0:18:50.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have been told that you\Ndesire to do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.54,0:18:52.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.46,0:18:58.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been told how you met\Nand fell in love with Alexis Doucet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.09,0:19:00.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's all in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.35,0:19:03.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not kid ourselves, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:19.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if it's only for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.03,0:19:22.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will make you my conquest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.08,0:19:24.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,H-How vulgar!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.46,0:19:32.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you sleep with me,\Nyou will have no claim over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.25,0:19:33.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I accept that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.17,0:19:37.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as a ritual for allies\Nabout to go to war together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.76,0:19:40.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.68,0:19:43.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, I have yet to be with a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.72,0:19:48.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be leaving everything to you.\NIs that acceptable?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.16,0:20:46.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will not pledge loyalty to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.95,0:20:49.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But from this moment on,\NI will become your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.21,0:20:54.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you march down the path\Nof military rule, I swear to fight by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.03,0:22:05.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,THE BLACK PRINCESS
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.04,0:23:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,EPISODE 10:\NBLADE OF BETRAYAL
